      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(synology-chat): truncate sanitized input on a UTF-16 boundary",
        "body": "## Problem\n`sanitizeInput` truncates long messages with `sanitized.slice(0, 4000)` on UTF-16 code units. When the 4000th unit lands inside a surrogate pair (e.g. an emoji), it keeps the high surrogate and drops the low one, leaving a lone surrogate.\n\n## Fix\nUse the shared `truncateUtf16Safe` helper so truncation stops on a whole code-point boundary.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in `extensions/synology-chat/src/core.test.ts` — fails before the fix, passes after. Pure unit test, no live account.\n",
